President Trump goes on vacation, critics sharpen their teeth.
It's vacation time - and that means a break for US President Donald Trump.
But with Trump being one of the most vacation-happy presidents ever, critics are already gritting their teeth.
According to USA Today and CNN, the president is planning a 17-day vacation at his namesake golf club in Bedminster, New Jersey.
Although the president's vacation began yesterday, Trump's opponents have been talking about it for weeks.
They're blaming Trump for resting too much.
In fact, it's customary for the president to spend weekends at his mansions in Florida, Virginia and New Jersey.
By the way, Trump is not the most rested president in his 196 days in office.
George W. Bush, for example, had already spent 67 days on vacation, while Barack Obama had spent only 21 days, half as many as Trump.
But Trump tends to forget things quickly.
Just days after taking office, Trump told "60 Minutes" that there would be no time for long vacations during his presidency because there was so much to do.
He also expressed outrage over Barack Obama's vacation three years ago.
The current president tweeted at the time, "While Obama is on vacation, playing golf, partying and attending jazz concerts, ISIS is beheading journalists".
According to White House officials, a 17-day visit to the golf club is not exactly relaxing.
It is officially called a working vacation, during which Trump has no time for reading or other pleasurable activities.
In addition, there had to be another reason for the leave.
Specifically, the air conditioning system in the West Wing of the White House is being replaced, and as a result, all personnel have been evacuated.
The West Wing is also home to the Oval Office and other presidential offices.
"I don't think any of you want to be in the West Wing in August when it's 100 degrees and there's no air conditioning", said White House spokeswoman Lindsay Walters, who stressed that the president will continue to work while on vacation.
