Wiranto, who has been accused by the UN of human rights crimes in connection with the deaths of more than 1,000 people in East Timor during the bloody 1999 independence referendum, said 11 human rights crimes had already been solved in Papua, including the one in Paniai.
The families of Paniai's victims greeted such claims with grim disbelief.
