A suicide bomber has attacked a military convoy in the Afghan capital of Kabul, killing one NATO soldier and wounding several others, officials say.
A NATO statement said five soldiers and an interpreter were wounded.
According to unconfirmed local reports, three civilians were also killed in the incident in the Qarabaghi district of the city.
The bombing is the latest in a spate of violence to hit Afghanistan this month, with more than 30 people killed in an attack on a mosque in Herat on Tuesday.
On Monday, a suicide bomber killed two people near the Iraqi embassy in Kabul.
A NATO statement said Thursday night's explosion occurred when a joint patrol with the Afghan army was attacked by "a man carrying a homemade explosive device".
