The end of the age of oil may also bring suffering to platinum.
Last year, about half of this precious metal was used in catalytic converters for diesel-powered cars, according to Johnson Matthey, a metal refiner.
"Many commodities that are currently in high demand, such as oil and platinum, may not be in high demand in the future", said Bernard Dahdah, a commodities analyst at Natixis.
This does not mean that raw materials as a whole will become less important, but their importance will change over 15 years.
